---
import InstallStep from './InstallStep.astro';
---
<!-- Installation Section -->
<section class="py-24 px-8 md:px-24 bg-surface">
<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-16">
<div class="reveal md:w-1/3">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-black uppercase mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
<span class="h-8 w-2 bg-primary"></span>
                    INSTALLATION
                </h2>
<p class="text-on-surface-variant mb-8 leading-relaxed">
                    The ritual of installation is the first step of the struggle. Follow the sequence precisely. No graphical installers. No hand-holding.
                </p>
<div class="space-y-4">
<InstallStep number="01" title="DOWNLOAD THE ISO" active={true} />
<InstallStep number="02" title="START THE INSTALLER" />
<InstallStep number="03" title="DONE." />
</div>
</div>
<div class="reveal reveal-delay-200 md:w-2/3 bg-surface-container-lowest border border-primary/30 relative">
<div class="bg-surface-container-high px-4 py-2 flex items-center justify-between border-b border-primary/20">
<div class="flex gap-2">
<div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary"></div>
<div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary/40"></div>
<div class="w-3 h-3 bg-primary/20"></div>
</div>
<span class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-primary font-bold">terminal — root@berserkarch</span>
</div>
<pre class="p-8 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto text-on-surface-variant m-0"><code><span class="text-primary font-bold">guts@berserkarch</span> ~ $ <span class="text-on-surface">berserk</span>
Package Manager for Security Tools, always from original sources, always latest.

<span class="text-on-surface">Usage:</span>
  berserk [flags]
  berserk [command]

<span class="text-on-surface">Available Commands:</span>
  <span class="text-primary">doctor</span>      Verify all installer backends are available
  <span class="text-primary">install</span>     Install one or more tools
  <span class="text-primary">list</span>        List tools, profiles, categories, or Docker container groups
  <span class="text-primary">remove</span>      Remove one or more installed tools
  <span class="text-primary">run</span>         Run a Docker container from the catalog
  <span class="text-primary">search</span>      Search the catalog for tools you can install
  <span class="text-primary">self-update</span> Update berserk itself to the latest release
  <span class="text-primary">sync</span>        Sync tools catalog (clone if absent, pull if present)
  <span class="text-primary">update</span>      Update tools to latest versions

<span class="text-on-surface">Flags:</span>
      --config string   config directory holding config.yaml and tool catalog yaml files
      --docker-clean    stop all containers, remove all images, prune
  -h, --help            help for berserk
  -v, --version         version for berserk
  -y, --yes             assume yes to system pkg mgr prompts (pacman --noconfirm / apt -y)

Use "berserk [command] --help" for more information about a command.
<span class="text-primary font-bold">guts@berserkarch</span> ~ $ <span class="animate-pulse text-primary font-bold">_</span></code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</section>
